cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.NI, cs.IT 

The paper deals with the transmission and optimization of virtual reality video streaming, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for encoding and rendering the video, as well as graphics (cs.GR) for the immersive experience. The optimization problem involves bandwidth and storage constraints, which are related to networking (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT).
